main event: Multiple, distinct, luminous objects were sighted in the sky over Hamburg, New York on February 6, 1969. The objects exhibited erratic, rapid movements and changed direction abruptly.
interesting points: The objects were roughly circular in shape, with estimated sizes ranging from 15 to 25 feet in diameter.
The objects displayed varying intensities of light, from dim to very bright.
The objects were observed maneuvering at high speeds, making sudden stops, and changing directions at sharp angles.
No sound was reported associated with the objects.
The witnesses were unable to determine the exact altitude of the objects, but estimated they were between 500 and 1,000 feet above the ground.
sighted object: multiple, distinct, luminous objects in the sky
witnesses: three adult witnesses - two males and one female
photographs: yes, the report includes two photographs of the sighting
